<span id="v.vi.xvii"></span>

<span id="v.vi.xvii-p1"></span> 16. For there were even in the Apostles’
times some who preached the truth not in truth, that is, not with
truthful mind: of whom the Apostle saith that they preached Christ not
chastely, but of envy and strife. And on this account even at that time
some were tolerated while preaching truth not with a chaste mind: yet
not any have been praised as preaching falsehood with a chaste mind.
Lastly, he saith of those, “Whether in pretence or in truth Christ be
preached:” <span id="fr_2403"></span>[2404](#fn_2403.md) but in no wise
would he say, In order that Christ may after be preached, let Him be
first denied.

